---
import WebsiteLayout from "../../../layouts/WhiteWebsiteLayout.astro";

import katex from "katex";
import "katex/dist/katex.min.css";

const equation = "y = mx + b";
const html = katex.renderToString(equation, { throwOnError: false });

const taylor_equation = "f(x) = \\sum_{n=0}^{\\infty} \\frac{f^{(n)}(a)}{n!} (x-a)^n";
const html_1 = katex.renderToString(taylor_equation, { throwOnError: false });

const first_dy_dx = "\\frac{dy}{dx} = x - y";
const html_2 = katex.renderToString(first_dy_dx, { throwOnError: false });

const K = (latex: "string") =>
  katex.renderToString(latex, { throwOnError: false });

---
<WebsiteLayout>
<main class="post">

<h1 class="post-title">
Toricelli's Law of Fluid Flow
</h1>
<nav> 
  <a href="/">index</a> /
      <a href="/about">about</a> /
      <a href="/math">math</a>
</nav>

<ul class="main-list">
  <li class="main-item">
    <p>
      (a) Show that the standard gravity differential equation 
      <span set:html={K("\\frac{d^2h}{dt^2} = -g")}></span> 
      implies that an object dropped from height 
      <span set:html={K("h(0)")}></span> 
      lands with velocity 
      <span set:html={K("-\\sqrt{2gh(0)}")}></span>.
    </p>

    <ul class="sub-list">
      <li class="sub-item">
        <p>
          We solve this by integrating:
        </p>

        <div class="math-block">
          <span set:html={K("\\frac{dh}{dt} = -gt + C_1")}></span>
        </div>

        <div class="math-block">
          <span set:html={K("h(t) = -\\frac{1}{2}gt^2 + C_1 t + C_2")}></span>
        </div>

        <p>
          Apply the initial condition that the object is dropped:
        </p>

        <div class="math-block">
          <span set:html={K("v(0)=0 \\Rightarrow C_1 = 0")}></span>
        </div>

        <p>
          So:
        </p>

        <div class="math-block">
          <span set:html={K("\\frac{dh}{dt} = -gt")}></span>
        </div>

        <div class="math-block">
          <span set:html={K("h(t) = h_0 - \\frac{1}{2}gt^2")}></span>
        </div>

        <p>
          Solve for <span set:html={K("t")}></span> and substitute back:
        </p>

        <div class="math-block">
          <span set:html={K("v = -\\sqrt{2g(h_0 - h)}")}></span>
        </div>

      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    (b)


  </li>
  <li> 
    (c) The conical tank has a radius of 20 cm when it's filled to an initial depth of 50cm. A small round hole at the bottom has a diameter of 1cm. Determine A(h) and a then solve the differential equation <span set:html={K("A(h)\\frac{dh}{dt} = -a * \\sqrt{2*g*h}")}> </span>
    and relate time and the height if the water. 
      <ul>
        <div> 
    <li> 
        Let's do integration <span set:html={K("\\int{A(h)*dh/dt = \\int{-a*\\sqrt{2*g*h}}}")}></span> and then  </span>
    </li>
  </ul>
  </div> 
  </li>

</ul>

</main>

<style>
main {
  max-width: 720px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 2rem 1rem;
  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.65;
  color: #000;
}

/* Title */
h1 {
  font-size: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

/* Sections */
.section {
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

/* Remove bullets completely */
ul {
  list-style: none;
  padding-left: 0;
  margin: 0;
}

li {
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

/* Indented blocks instead of bullets */
.indent {
  margin-left: 1rem;
}

/* Math spacing */
.math-block {
  display: block;
  margin: 0.4rem 0;
}

/* Clean solution block */
.solution {
  border-left: 3px solid #000;
  padding-left: 0.8rem;
  margin-top: 0.6rem;
}

/* Slight emphasis */
strong {
  font-weight: 600;
}
</style>

</WebsiteLayout>